git repository: maint

http://www.apachehaus.com/downloads/httpd-2.4.7-x86.zip

The ApacheHaus binaries are built with VC9 - so run more generally.

Step 1: generate env.conf or copy from the 'build' directory of agent.

From the top-level directory of this repo i.e. the one containing this README:

bash:
INSTALLDIR=`pwd` DATADIR=`pwd` LISTEN_PORT=8889 ./apache2/bin/httpd.exe -f /path/to/conf/httpd.conf

cmd.exe:
set INSTALLDIR=%cd% && set DATADIR=%cd% && set LISTEN_PORT=8889 && apache2 \bin\httpd.exe -f drive:\path\to\conf\httpd.conf

NOTE: in both cases specify the full path to the conf file (or have the shell do so)

--- old setup --

extract the zip file into the top-level of the maint repo

mv Apache24/htdocs Apache24/_htdocs
mkdir Apache24/htdocs


bash:
TOPDIR=`pwd` ./Apache24/bin/httpd.exe -f ../conf/httpd.conf

cmd.exe:
set TOPDIR=%cd% && Apache24\bin\httpd.exe -f ..\conf\httpd.conf

